<TITLE> Ctg BNP bosses for running polls </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 13 (bdnews24.com)--Top BNP leaders of Chittagong on Thursday were unanimous that the party will run the June 17 mayoral polls. The decision came from a meeting of the at Gulshan's Lake Shore Hotel, said Chittagong (North) BNP president Giasuddin Quader Chowdhury. He told bdnews24.com, "We have decided to contest the polls as a part of our movement against the government." He also said standing committee member Salahuddin Quader Chowdhury MP and BNP advisory panel member Amir Khashru Mahmud Chowdhury will inform party chairperson Khaleda Zia of the decision. "A decision has been taken on the probable mayor candidate. The chairperson will also be informed of the decision," Kader said, refusing to name that candidate. He, however, said the party's vice-president Abdullah Al Noman was not present at the meeting. The meeting, attended by top Chittagong BNP leaders including Salahuddin Qader and Amir Khashru, started around 6.30pm. Earlier on Thursday, BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain told journalists that the final decision about his party's participation in the mayor polls would be taken after discussion with Khaleda. bdne
